// DesignContextMenu
// Right-click context menu for the design canvas. Provides node operations:
// Duplicate, Delete, Group, Ungroup, Bring to Front, Send to Back, Flip H/V,
// and alignment/distribution actions.
// Clamps position to stay within the viewport.

FUNCTION DesignContextMenu() -> JSX | null                             EXPORT
  Reads contextMenu position and selectedIds from designEditorStore.
  Returns null when contextMenu is null.
  Clamps menu position to viewport bounds in a useEffect.
  Window click dismisses menu; Escape dismisses menu.
  Menu items are conditionally shown based on selection:
    Group: shown when ≥2 nodes selected.
    Ungroup: shown when selected node isGroup.
    Flip H/V: shown when ≥2 nodes selected.
    Align (6 directions): shown when ≥2 selected.
    Distribute H/V: shown when ≥3 selected.

---

FUNCTION handleClick(e) -> void
  Dismisses context menu on any window click.

---

FUNCTION handleKeyDown(e) -> void
  Escape key dismisses context menu.
